title: Poxi: A Modern GeoCities
Show HN: I created a site to make AI generated photos of your pet
text:
Hey HN,
I have Goats and a camel as my pets and I recently saw some very cool AI-generated pictures so I decided to build a startup with my 19 y/o brother where you can generate these AI photos for your pet.
I thought this could be a cool idea for crazy pet owners who want to create new memories with their pet or to get new photos of a deceased pet.
Let me know if you have any feedback or questions!

title: Ask HN: Search engine specific for intent/meaning
text:
Do any search engines exclude common phrases from their results?

I'm looking for an app in HN comments and whatever combination of words often includes common phrases such as "that is a stretch", "home stretch" etc that are quite obviously irrelevant.

Eg: https://hn.algolia.com/?dateRange=pastYear&page=0&prefix=true&query=app%20stretch&sort=byPopularity&type=comment

I imagine Algolia is possibly one of the better search indexing tools, and the thought occurred, maybe a bit of a stretch, that this would be a useful noise reducing filter. Probably over-simplifying an entire engineering domain.

Ask HN: Are you using open source solutions to secure your SDLC?
text:
Hey community, I’m trying to research the use of open-source in the security space (especially for securing SDLC) and figured this would be a good place to start.

I have a few questions on top of that: 1. Do you use open source in your company and what is your process for approving an open-source solution? 2. Does your company secure its SDLC (software development life cycle)? 3. What tools do you use to keep your SDLC secure? 4. In your opinion, what are the biggest pros and cons of using open-source tools in cybersecurity?

Thank you so much!
